<p>Installation costs vary based on roof complexity, electrical upgrades required, and local permitting fees. Simple single-story ranch homes with south-facing roofs represent the most cost-effective installations, while multi-story homes with complex rooflines or significant shading issues require additional engineering and equipment. Ground-mounted systems typically cost 10-15% more than rooftop installations but may be necessary for properties with unsuitable roof conditions or excessive shading.</p>

<h2>HVAC Systems in Illinois</h2>

